1
00:21:48,231 --> 00:21:54,161
Warren’s words have really moved my heart,
and if England is my heart, England should

2
00:21:54,161 --> 00:22:09,331
also feel moved: that’s the spirit of Shri
Ganesh.

3
00:22:09,331 --> 00:22:22,231
And I must say that I have seen so many things
in Warren, which are very heartening.

4
00:22:22,231 --> 00:22:37,191
Whenever I have felt desperate about things,
you see, seeing him I felt I must do something

5
00:22:37,191 --> 00:22:54,430
more, because he really loves me very much,
I have seen that, with complete selfless dedication.

6
00:22:54,430 --> 00:23:09,201
But dedication is a word which doesn’t have
that beauty of love.

7
00:23:09,201 --> 00:23:18,981
I mean if I’m sitting down he’ll immediately
worry if I have got the tea, or if I need

8
00:23:18,981 --> 00:23:25,780
some heating, or little things here and there,
and I watch — I’m surprised.

9
00:23:25,780 --> 00:23:34,460
Like any other Sahaj Yogi he’ll be jumping
up here and there and finding out things to

10
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:36,621
adjust.

11
00:23:36,621 --> 00:23:48,710
And even if I really once say that, “Maybe,”
he just doesn’t do it, just doesn’t do

12
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:49,710
it.

13
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:50,921
He said, “That’s it, settled!”

14
00:23:50,921 --> 00:23:56,031
I have never seen him asking me to give him
time to meet him, never.

15
00:23:56,031 --> 00:24:02,630
Not even once he said, “Mother I must come
and see you!” nothing, never!

16
00:24:02,630 --> 00:24:12,711
I have not known how much money he spent all
throughout his trip.

17
00:24:12,711 --> 00:24:15,351
I don’t know, really.

18
00:24:15,351 --> 00:24:21,401
And I was wanting somebody to say that, “Mother
we must pay for his travel!” because he’s

19
00:24:21,401 --> 00:24:25,651
really spent all his money.

20
00:24:25,651 --> 00:24:31,211
And I was happy that David brought this point
to me, I was very happy.

21
00:24:31,211 --> 00:24:46,630
One thing I feel [is] that you cannot ask
for love, that’s something you cannot do.

22
00:24:46,630 --> 00:24:56,061
It’s a very difficult thing to ask somebody
to love, but that, I think, is the point one

23
00:24:56,061 --> 00:24:57,220
should see.

24
00:24:57,220 --> 00:25:08,160
When you think of Shri Ganesh, you just have
to know that He loves the Mother so much that

25
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:15,213
even a slightest hint, He knows what I want,
He knows.

26
00:25:15,213 --> 00:25:19,951
He knows me too well.

27
00:25:19,951 --> 00:25:34,041
He’s not at all so compassionate as myself,
because He cannot forgive those who try to

28
00:25:34,041 --> 00:25:36,701
insult me, He cannot.

29
00:25:36,701 --> 00:25:42,061
Those who try to cheat me, those who try to
be arrogant or egoistical.

30
00:25:42,061 --> 00:25:47,500
He doesn’t, he doesn’t believe in that,
He cannot.

31
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:48,500
He wants to punish.

32
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:54,151
He’s ready to punish, very anxious to punish
such people.

33
00:25:54,151 --> 00:25:55,651
But if I say, “No.

34
00:25:55,651 --> 00:25:58,811
Spare him,” He listens to me.

35
00:25:58,811 --> 00:26:07,391
That’s His quality: He cannot bear anything
against me, cannot bear!

36
00:26:07,391 --> 00:26:15,091
And left to Him, I think I don’t know how
many Sahaj Yogis would have been there.

37
00:26:15,091 --> 00:26:20,001
Even to say, “No Mother!” itself, He cuts
you out on that point.

38
00:26:20,001 --> 00:26:28,721
But I don’t want that it should happen,
because He doesn’t know that you are still

39
00:26:28,721 --> 00:26:35,781
needing help, and attention, and tremendous
compassion.

40
00:26:35,781 --> 00:26:42,231
But you can only know your Mother through
shraddha, through faith.

41
00:26:42,231 --> 00:26:46,181
And what he says is true.

42
00:26:46,181 --> 00:26:47,881
And why this faith?

43
00:26:47,881 --> 00:26:54,791
I mean you see miracles every day, not only
today: such games, such play, such things

44
00:26:54,791 --> 00:27:01,321
going on; how I have been able to express
myself slowly.

45
00:27:01,321 --> 00:27:03,401
I don’t want to give you any shocks.

46
00:27:03,401 --> 00:27:18,621
So in a very beautiful manner I have tried
to bring forth the play of the Divine.

47
00:27:18,621 --> 00:27:26,651
But I feel that, even now, people get into
arguments: if I say, “No, this won’t work

48
00:27:26,651 --> 00:27:27,651
out.

49
00:27:27,651 --> 00:27:32,581
That’s not good,” I have to spend at least
four, five hours going round and round and

50
00:27:32,581 --> 00:27:39,171
bringing the point to the heads of people
that, “No, that’s not good, that won’t

51
00:27:39,171 --> 00:27:40,521
help you."

52
00:27:40,521 --> 00:27:42,581
But once I asked him, “How is it you are
so obedient?”

53
00:27:42,581 --> 00:27:46,091
I mean, whatever I say he, just he gets a
hint, he’ll agree.

54
00:27:46,091 --> 00:27:51,131
He said, “Mother I once learned a lesson:
that’s my own marriage.

55
00:27:51,131 --> 00:27:56,721
And you didn’t say no, but you did say to
me that, ‘If it makes you happy.’

56
00:27:56,721 --> 00:28:01,421
you didn’t say, ‘It will make you joyous,’
and I have learned a lesson from that."

57
00:28:01,421 --> 00:28:04,861
But we don’t learn our lessons is [what]
the point is.

58
00:28:04,861 --> 00:28:13,141
We don’t learn our lessons.

59
00:28:13,141 --> 00:28:18,861
We argue: that comes from ego.

60
00:28:18,861 --> 00:28:23,031
If we have superego we, we make others mad!

61
00:28:23,031 --> 00:28:31,181
Like somebody came from America and he was
just mad that he must come and see me.

62
00:28:31,181 --> 00:28:33,261
And I’m so busy, I have no time, you know
that.

63
00:28:33,261 --> 00:28:35,531
I have to correct this book, I have to correct
that book.

64
00:28:35,531 --> 00:28:39,041
Now we have to do this Advent, and that is
to be done.

65
00:28:39,041 --> 00:28:43,521
I have to look after my household, and this
and that.

66
00:28:43,521 --> 00:28:46,171
I am so busy.

67
00:28:46,171 --> 00:28:49,331
But the person really made them mad, that
he must see me!

68
00:28:49,331 --> 00:28:53,141
Now if you come from America, that doesn’t
mean that you must see me, because you never

69
00:28:53,141 --> 00:28:54,331
took time with me.

70
00:28:54,331 --> 00:28:56,431
I am busy here now.

71
00:28:56,431 --> 00:29:03,751
When I went to America, it’s all right,
which is true.

72
00:29:03,751 --> 00:29:10,471
And we do not realise that what we are doing
[is] that we don’t love Mother, we don’t

73
00:29:10,471 --> 00:29:11,471
love Her.

74
00:29:11,471 --> 00:29:17,231
We think of our needs, our impressions, our
talking, it’s a fact.

75
00:29:17,231 --> 00:29:22,251
Like somebody I asked, “All right you speak,
you are a good speaker."

76
00:29:22,251 --> 00:29:26,351
All right, the person starts speaking, and
he becomes egoistical.

77
00:29:26,351 --> 00:29:31,761
How can you be?

78
00:29:31,761 --> 00:29:35,521
If you just start giving a good speech, you
become egoistical.

79
00:29:35,521 --> 00:29:38,381
Somebody made good photographs, so I said,
“These are good photographs."

80
00:29:38,381 --> 00:29:39,381
He becomes egoistical!

81
00:29:39,381 --> 00:29:42,891
You cannot praise anyone in this country — it’s
the worst thing [for them].

82
00:29:42,891 --> 00:29:43,901
He says, “Agnya is clear."

83
00:29:43,901 --> 00:29:47,581
I don’t know what sort of an Agnya is clear
here! you cannot praise.

84
00:29:47,581 --> 00:29:48,761
I mean I try to be nice.

85
00:29:48,761 --> 00:29:50,931
I say, “Oh your photographs are very nice."

86
00:29:50,931 --> 00:29:54,191
Immediately the person becomes egoistical.

87
00:29:54,191 --> 00:29:58,201
You give some work to someone, “All right
you do this work, postering."

88
00:29:58,201 --> 00:30:01,111
Somebody is doing that: his ego goes up!

89
00:30:01,111 --> 00:30:02,111
What is this?

90
00:30:02,111 --> 00:30:03,961
Like a balloon?

91
00:30:03,961 --> 00:30:05,911
There’s no depth.

92
00:30:05,911 --> 00:30:07,851
There’s no gravity.

93
00:30:07,851 --> 00:30:09,151
Now why?

94
00:30:09,151 --> 00:30:10,151
This is the question.

95
00:30:10,151 --> 00:30:13,271
He asked me many a times, “Why it happens
Mother?”

96
00:30:13,271 --> 00:30:19,580
The reason is — I told them the other day,
I think they have a tape on this; you can

97
00:30:19,580 --> 00:30:25,621
go through that — a simple thing is that,
that we have lived a superficial life here.

98
00:30:25,621 --> 00:30:29,080
We are superficial people.

99
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:36,641
Because the society is such, this machine
has made us like this, and we have read books.

100
00:30:36,641 --> 00:30:37,840
We have pampered egos.

101
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:42,051
Our forefathers went and fought in other countries
thinking no end of themselves.

102
00:30:42,051 --> 00:30:44,400
Then we had this war.

103
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:50,101
With the war we became also nonsensical, either
aggressive, or we have become with superego.

104
00:30:50,101 --> 00:30:51,351
We have bhoots.

105
00:30:51,351 --> 00:30:53,460
We have conditionings.

106
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:54,700
All these things are there.

107
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:58,510
We are not our genuine self, is the point.

108
00:30:58,510 --> 00:31:07,531
So I think the being that is going to be enlightened
by your Spirit is covered with ego, and on

109
00:31:07,531 --> 00:31:12,281
top of that is a sheen of that superficial
being that you are.

110
00:31:12,281 --> 00:31:15,421
So Mother says [something] — “All right!”

111
00:31:15,421 --> 00:31:17,460
Mother did this — ”All right!”

112
00:31:17,460 --> 00:31:20,831
Nothing goes inside I feel.

113
00:31:20,831 --> 00:31:24,090
There’s no love.

114
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:28,931
If you are in love with someone, even if the
person is in that vicinity anywhere…you

115
00:31:28,931 --> 00:31:31,700
know Mother is in London, just think, “Mother
is in London."

116
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:32,700
Just think!

117
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:34,741
If you love me, just think.

118
00:31:34,741 --> 00:31:42,391
What a happy thought it is: “She’s in
England!”

119
00:31:42,391 --> 00:31:49,551
It’s a happy thought.

120
00:31:49,551 --> 00:31:50,551
Think on those lines.

121
00:31:50,551 --> 00:31:56,590
But it does not work out because that genuine
thing, the genuine thing that is inside, is

122
00:31:56,590 --> 00:31:59,171
covered with ego or superego.

123
00:31:59,171 --> 00:32:01,971
your bhoots are in between.

124
00:32:01,971 --> 00:32:07,650
So what happens [is] that you live with that
superficial nonsense.

125
00:32:07,650 --> 00:32:08,650
Nothing goes inside.

126
00:32:08,650 --> 00:32:13,801
It’s all [at] that level.

127
00:32:13,801 --> 00:32:18,691
You ask anyone, they’ll say, “I’m all
right.

128
00:32:18,691 --> 00:32:20,621
I’m like this."

129
00:32:20,621 --> 00:32:21,621
Why?

130
00:32:21,621 --> 00:32:23,700
Nothing goes inside, why?

131
00:32:23,700 --> 00:32:28,051
Because, the genuine self is lost.

132
00:32:28,051 --> 00:32:32,471
What is going to enlighten you is not your
artificial thing.

133
00:32:32,471 --> 00:32:42,101
You know artificial fibre, if you have artificial
fibre, it doesn’t penetrate anything.

134
00:32:42,101 --> 00:32:47,161
It can penetrate into everything, but nothing
can penetrate into it.

135
00:32:47,161 --> 00:32:54,281
Like that, that artificial thing on us, and
we live with it, all the time.

136
00:32:54,281 --> 00:32:59,510
Now why he said about Maharashtra [is] because
Maharashtrians are not exposed to artificiality,

137
00:32:59,510 --> 00:33:00,941
they don’t know what is artificiality.

138
00:33:00,941 --> 00:33:05,721
People think they are stupid, they are foolish,
they are no good for business, they are not

139
00:33:05,721 --> 00:33:08,250
good for this, they are not good for that.

140
00:33:08,250 --> 00:33:14,650
But the main thing is that their genuine being
is not covered with any nonsenses: “I am

141
00:33:14,650 --> 00:33:16,791
something!”

142
00:33:16,791 --> 00:33:21,221
I have never seen Warren feeling that way,
and that’s something surprising.

143
00:33:21,221 --> 00:33:27,960
I have never seen him feeling that he’s
important, that he should be near me, he should

144
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,271
be in my company — never!

145
00:33:29,271 --> 00:33:35,090
Never even I have heard him anywhere around.

146
00:33:35,090 --> 00:33:38,770
I have to call for him.

147
00:33:38,770 --> 00:33:44,370
Unless and until I call him, he’ll never
come before me.

148
00:33:44,370 --> 00:33:50,510
He wants to see if I need him, otherwise he’s
not bothered.

149
00:33:50,510 --> 00:33:55,881
He just feels that I’m around, “Mother
is somewhere."

150
00:33:55,881 --> 00:33:59,411
Unless and until [I call him].

151
00:33:59,411 --> 00:34:02,991
But if I tell him, “Warren I want…”
wherever he may be, he’ll just rush and

152
00:34:02,991 --> 00:34:03,991
come.

153
00:34:03,991 --> 00:34:04,991
It’s a very good example for you.

154
00:34:04,991 --> 00:34:06,900
I am happy there are some examples of this
kind.

155
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:14,171
There are many others; I am not saying it’s
only Warren.

156
00:34:14,171 --> 00:34:20,361
And then, if you take up any responsibility
in Sahaj Yoga, then you start thinking you

157
00:34:20,361 --> 00:34:24,640
are great, you are a great Sahaj Yogi: you
have done this, you have put the postering,

158
00:34:24,640 --> 00:34:26,210
you have done this.

159
00:34:26,210 --> 00:34:33,640
This shows the calibre, shows the calibre.

160
00:34:33,640 --> 00:34:41,801
People from absolutely dead conditions have
risen so high, and while people from quite

161
00:34:41,801 --> 00:34:46,551
normal conditions are nowhere there, just
they are just there, why?

162
00:34:46,551 --> 00:34:47,551
The Calibre.

163
00:34:47,551 --> 00:34:49,671
Now everybody has that calibre.

164
00:34:49,671 --> 00:34:53,250
What I am trying to say: every one of us have
the calibre.

165
00:34:53,250 --> 00:35:04,661
But it is not evident in everyone because
the amount of covering they have.

166
00:35:04,661 --> 00:35:10,101
Everybody has capacity to love, everyone has
capacity.

167
00:35:10,101 --> 00:35:15,601
But if you have covered yourself completely
with artificiality you cannot love.

168
00:35:15,601 --> 00:35:18,921
Now if you ask me, “Mother, how to love?”

169
00:35:18,921 --> 00:35:21,671
what am I to tell you?

170
00:35:21,671 --> 00:35:23,830
I love you, no doubt.

171
00:35:23,830 --> 00:35:26,291
I love all of you.

172
00:35:26,291 --> 00:35:29,351
I love you very much.

173
00:35:29,351 --> 00:35:31,191
I am bothered about you.

174
00:35:31,191 --> 00:35:37,301
But what I find then, when I am bothered about
somebody, that person starts taking advantage.

175
00:35:37,301 --> 00:35:45,601
I don’t mind [if you] take advantage, but
by taking advantage that person goes down

176
00:35:45,601 --> 00:35:47,791
completely.

177
00:35:47,791 --> 00:35:54,361
If I am bothered about something, then [that]
one immediately starts thinking they are very

178
00:35:54,361 --> 00:36:01,051
important, that, “Mother is so much bothered
about me!”

179
00:36:01,051 --> 00:36:11,890
Now try to understand that this is a country
which is my heart, is my heart itself.

180
00:36:11,890 --> 00:36:18,130
And Sahastrara is nothing else but it’s
heart.

181
00:36:18,130 --> 00:36:25,041
Have you noticed how it is nicely managed
already that, if Kundalini has to break, it

182
00:36:25,041 --> 00:36:29,070
has to break through the heart chakra?

183
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:34,770
If your heart is not all right, it cannot
break, your Kundalini at Sahastrara.

184
00:36:34,770 --> 00:36:36,960
Have you seen that?

185
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:49,380
That the Brahmarandhra, the last opening,
is on the heart chakra.

186
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:51,691
I know everyone very well.

187
00:36:51,691 --> 00:36:54,171
There are people who are mediums with us.

188
00:36:54,171 --> 00:36:57,001
I know that.

189
00:36:57,001 --> 00:37:00,330
But they don’t know they’ll go to Hell.

190
00:37:00,330 --> 00:37:05,471
It’s a very dangerous time you are in — be
careful!

191
00:37:05,471 --> 00:37:15,661
And that makes me feel even worse when I think
that they don’t know on what horrible times

192
00:37:15,661 --> 00:37:22,361
your feet are dangling.

193
00:37:22,361 --> 00:37:25,241
So don’t play games!

194
00:37:25,241 --> 00:37:34,140
I know English language has its own styles
and things, English mannerism has its own

195
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:35,911
ways, methods.

196
00:37:35,911 --> 00:37:41,691
Forget that you are English!|

197
00:37:41,691 --> 00:37:48,700
That’s the best way.

198
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:54,070
English think that, “We are different people.

199
00:37:54,070 --> 00:37:59,551
We are of the heart you see — great people!”

200
00:37:59,551 --> 00:38:03,250
In Italy I told one journalist lady who had
come, very good lady.

201
00:38:03,250 --> 00:38:07,430
She said, “Mother one thing I didn’t like
the sentence you said that, ‘England is

202
00:38:07,430 --> 00:38:08,460
the heart.’

203
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:12,161
Agh, how can it be?

204
00:38:12,161 --> 00:38:13,161
Horrible?”

205
00:38:13,161 --> 00:38:15,851
She couldn’t believe it.

206
00:38:15,851 --> 00:38:20,650
She said, “Only because you said I tolerate
it, but anybody else saying it I would not

207
00:38:20,650 --> 00:38:21,851
tolerate!”

208
00:38:21,851 --> 00:38:35,210
So how far we have gone down as English, you
must see the reputation of English abroad.

209
00:38:35,210 --> 00:38:40,541
And advancement we have made is to reach the
status of punk rocks!

210
00:38:40,541 --> 00:38:53,551
So when there is such a situation in a country,
how serious we have to be about it.

211
00:38:53,551 --> 00:38:57,911
Because this country is going to save the
world or is going to mar the world, because

212
00:38:57,911 --> 00:38:59,841
it is at the Sahastrara.

213
00:38:59,841 --> 00:39:02,461
Where Mother is to be accepted.

214
00:39:02,461 --> 00:39:10,561
Whether Mother is to be settled and worshipped
and adored.

215
00:39:10,561 --> 00:39:20,071
But do we have that seriousness of understanding
that we are born at a time when the responsibility

216
00:39:20,071 --> 00:39:21,711
is much more on us?

217
00:39:21,711 --> 00:39:25,681
We don’t realise that we are born in the
heart, means our responsibility is much, much

218
00:39:25,681 --> 00:39:31,301
more than other people have.

219
00:39:31,301 --> 00:39:38,671
On the contrary, “We are born on the heart,
so we are great people!” — finished!

220
00:39:38,671 --> 00:39:47,671
There are certain things which you follow,
simple things, is going to help you.

221
00:39:47,671 --> 00:39:54,131
The other day I met somebody who had a nonsensical
thing like a Hamsa [catch].

222
00:39:54,131 --> 00:39:56,191
I said, “Hamsa, how can you have?

223
00:39:56,191 --> 00:39:57,571
Are you putting oil everyday?

224
00:39:57,571 --> 00:39:59,081
Are you putting ghee everyday?”

225
00:39:59,081 --> 00:40:00,111
He said, “No!”

226
00:40:00,111 --> 00:40:04,221
I said, “Why?

227
00:40:04,221 --> 00:40:10,291
Is a simple thing like that, why don’t you
do everyday?”

